section.text:
Title XVI of the International Financial
			 Institutions Act (22 U.S.C. 262p—262p–8) is further amended by adding at the
			 end the following:

paragraph.text:
adopt an integrated
				development strategy to support poverty reduction through economic growth, that
				includes monitorable poverty reduction goals;

implement transparent
				policy making and budget procedures, good governance, and effective
				anticorruption measures;

broaden public
				participation and popular understanding of the principles and goals of poverty
				reduction, particularly through economic growth, and good governance;
